{"ref_id": "group_2", "text": "

Across four consecutive episodes, the XR-7491 clinical trial program demonstrates parallel progress in Rheumatoid Arthritis (RA) and Cardiovascular (CV) studies with distinct site activations and safety events. In the RA Phase IIb trial (XR-7491-RA-002), CLINICAL OPS issued EMAIL-002 on 2025-03-15 to 24 Site PIs regarding Protocol Amendments 2.0, achieving 96% training access [clinical_trial_10_ep_005]. SITE-005 (RHEUMATOLOGY CLINICAL CENTER, PI_BROWN) activated on 2025-03-15, enrolling SUBJECT_010 and SUBJECT_011, bringing total randomization to 48 subjects (16% of 300 target) [clinical_trial_10_ep_005]. SITE-001 (METRO RHEUMATOLOGY ASSOCIATES, DR. ALICE WONG) recorded DOSE-003 for SUBJECT_001 [clinical_trial_10_ep_005]. By 2025-03-18, enrollment at SITE-006 (METRO RHEUMATOLOGY CENTER, PI_Lee) reached 58 subjects, with Subject_012 and Subject_013 randomized to 30mg and 15mg arms respectively [clinical_trial_10_ep_006]. Efficacy Report EFF-003 showed ACR20 rates of 60% for the 30mg arm [clinical_trial_10_ep_006].

Concurrently, the CV Phase III trial (XR-7491-CV-003) at SITE-005 (Dr. E. White) enrolled 140 subjects [clinical_trial_10_dx_cardiology_trial_005]. Subject SUB-005 experienced AE-005 (Hypotension, Grade 1) on 2023-09-10, resolved by 2023-09-15 [clinical_trial_10_dx_cardiology_trial_005]. In the subsequent CV episode (XR-7491-CV-301), SITE-006 (Regional Cardiovascular Research Center, Dr. F. Green) managed Subject SUB-006 [clinical_trial_10_dx_cardiology_trial_006]. On 2023-10-12, SUB-006 experienced AE-006 (Stroke Ischemic, Grade 2), requiring hospitalization at Regional General Hospital for 48 hours [clinical_trial_10_dx_cardiology_trial_006]. Dr. F. Green authorized unblinding Log-ID-994 for safety review [clinical_trial_10_dx_cardiology_trial_006]. Laboratory results for SUB-006 on 2023-10-12 remained within reference ranges (Creatinine 1.0, eGFR 75) [clinical_trial_10_dx_cardiology_trial_006]. Drug accountability for XR-7491-BATCH-2023-004 showed a balance of 0 tablets [clinical_trial_10_dx_cardiology_trial_006]. Safety reporting timelines were updated across protocols to require expedited SAE reporting within 24 hours [clinical_trial_10_ep_005].", "metadata": {"type": "group_summary", "episode_ids": ["clinical_trial_10_ep_005", "clinical_trial_10_dx_cardiology_trial_005", "clinical_trial_10_ep_006", "clinical_trial_10_dx_cardiology_trial_006"]}}
